I noticed the for-loop is used for all the backtracing questions. It is fine. However, it's more intuitive if each recursion focuses on itself - choose or not choose.

The non for-loop is a general solution if you don't need to leap and inspect all other elements in the dataset.

Use this question as example. Here's the code:
```
class Solution {
    public List<List<Integer>> subsetsWithDup(int[] nums) {
        List<List<Integer>> ret = new ArrayList<>();
        Arrays.sort(nums);
        subset(nums, 0, new ArrayList<>(), ret);
        return ret;
    }

    private void subset(int[] nums, int index, List<Integer> parts, List<List<Integer>> ret) {
        if(index == nums.length) {
            ret.add(new ArrayList<>(parts));
            return;
        }
        parts.add(nums[index]);
        subset(nums, index+1, parts, ret);
        parts.remove(parts.size()-1);

        while(index+1 < nums.length && nums[index+1] == nums[index]) {
            ++index;
        }
        subset(nums, index+1, parts, ret);
    }
}
```

