**Solution:**

1. Consider every subsequence as a collection of `bits`.
2. 0, 1, 10, 11, 100, 101, 110, 111, and so on.
3. We can observe that every `set bit(1)` indicates that we must include that particular element present in the array `nums` and every `unset bit(0)` indicates we must ignore that element.
4. Check for every number which particular bit is set or unset using `i & (1 << j)`. This formula helps us to know whether to include a particular element or not.

