```
//approach: backtracking(dfs)
//basic template of backtracking would be to loop, choose, explore and unchoose
//loop: you want to iterate over all the numbers so that you can find it's possible values
//choose: you start with the index value(the 0th index number), so that you can find the next combined possible values for the 0th value
//explore: basically recursion to add all the next values to the 0th value
//unchoose: you pop the value (Oth value), so then you can now start with other value to make that other value 0th value
//in this case: 
//when drawing the recursive tree, we can see that,
//               = we can take each element from the nums array and recurse down until we are at the end of the length of the nums array
//               = after recursing the element we are on, we can move on to the next element in the array and continue till the i < nums array.length
//we pass in index so that we can reset i when we want to, however i will most likely be ahead of the index value, when we recurse back
//
//before we backtrack: 
//we will sort the the given array in ascending order which is time of (nlogn)  (i might be wrong about the time complexity, but 95% sure)
//and doing so, we can always check if the previous value is the same as the current value while iterating, 
//we will be adding the value as we iterate on to the subsets array, but just not when we encounter the same value we previously saw
var subsetsWithDup = function(nums) {
    nums = nums.sort((a,b)=> a-b);
    let resultArray = new Array();

    function helper(nums, subSets, index){
        resultArray.push([...subSets]);

        for(let i = index; i < nums.length; i++){

            //making sure i > 0  so when we subtract nums[i - 1] we dont get nums[-1]
            //to avoid going back to duplicate sets, we can check previous value is not equal to the same value  nums[i-1] === nums[i]
            if(i > index && nums[i-1] === nums[i]) 
                continue;

            //choose
            subSets.push(nums[i]);

            //explore
            helper(nums, subSets, i+1);

            //unchoose
            subSets.pop();

        }
    }
    helper(nums, new Array(), 0);

    return resultArray;
};
```

