Basically we need to construct our accumulator variable `res` shaving off the leftmost digit at each iteration and adding it to the double (`<< 1` works like `* 2` in this case) to our previously computed `res`; similarly, at each iteration we remove the just used leftmost bit with a right shift: `>> 1`.

