solutions.content:
The logic is to push 1 bit at a time from end of one register to another.

Consider a 4 bit number n = 1101, result = 0000
1) First iteration: result = 0000 ( after left shift of 1), n & 1 = 0001 (since n is odd), result | n & 1 = 0001, n >> 1 right shifts n, now n = 0110. You can see last bit of n in now added to result.
2) Second iteration: result = 0010 (left shift of 1), n & 1 = 0000 (n is even), result | (n&1) = 0010, n >> 1 gives n = 0011
3) Third iteration: result = 0100, n & 1 = 0001, result | (n & 1) = 0101, n >> 1 = 0001
4) Fourth iteration: result = 1010, n & 1 = 0001, result | (n & 1) = 1011, n >> 1 = 0000

In this way, we remove element from right side of n and append it to result, then we push result to 1 bit left. 

