# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
store all the strings of s into a vector.
Create two maps for two way mapping. Traverse the pattern and check both ways that is if current character is not present in map1 and current string is not present in map2 then insert `{ch,str}` in map1 and `{str,ch}` in map 2. now if curr character or current string is already present in map1 or map2 respectively and its value is not matching then return false.
 **Dry run on** `pattern = "abba", s = "dog dog dog dog"`
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
    O(nlog(n)), n is the size of pattern.
- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
    O(m) m is the size of s.
